18
00:00:12,582 --> 00:00:15,582
http://hiqve.com/

19
00:00:17,606 --> 00:00:19,566
<i>A flaw in the plan!</i>

20
00:00:19,649 --> 00:00:21,651
<i>While in the middle of a heated battle,</i>

21
00:00:21,735 --> 00:00:25,906
<i>Clone Trooper Tup lost his senses
and killed a Jedi general.</i>

22
00:00:25,989 --> 00:00:28,325
<i>Seeming to have
no awareness of his actions,</i>

23
00:00:28,408 --> 00:00:31,328
<i>Tup's health
began to deteriorate rapidly.</i>

24
00:00:31,411 --> 00:00:33,872
<i>Fearing the illness was
linked to a Separatist plot,</i>

25
00:00:33,955 --> 00:00:38,460
<i>Anakin Skywalker has dispatched
Captain Rex and ARC Trooper 5555</i>

26
00:00:38,543 --> 00:00:41,463
<i>to escort Tup back
to the cloning facilities on Kamino</i>

27
00:00:41,546 --> 00:00:43,715
<i>for an intensive evaluation.</i>

28
00:01:16,039 --> 00:01:18,833
You will have to say goodbye
to your friend now.

29
00:01:18,917 --> 00:01:20,919
Yes, Doctor.

30
00:01:21,002 --> 00:01:22,420
General Shaak Ti.

31
00:01:22,504 --> 00:01:23,922
Captain Rex.

32
00:01:24,589 --> 00:01:26,508
Fives. Am I correct?

33
00:01:26,591 --> 00:01:27,926
Yes, General.

34
00:01:29,261 --> 00:01:30,929
You've served with Tup?

35
00:01:31,012 --> 00:01:32,055
Yes.

36
00:01:32,973 --> 00:01:34,391
You must come with me.

37
00:01:34,474 --> 00:01:38,061
With... With all due respect, General,

38
00:01:38,144 --> 00:01:39,980
I can't just abandon him now.

39
00:01:40,230 --> 00:01:42,440
You must let the doctors do their work.

40
00:01:42,524 --> 00:01:46,236
Do not be afraid.
Your friend is in quite capable hands.

41
00:01:46,319 --> 00:01:49,364
Dr. Nala Se is
the Chief Medical Scientist on Kamino.

42
00:01:49,698 --> 00:01:52,742
She was one of the primary engineers
of all the clones.

43
00:01:53,326 --> 00:01:55,161
Now, we must take care of you.

44
00:01:55,245 --> 00:01:57,956
Me? There's nothing
wrong with me, General.

45
00:01:58,039 --> 00:01:59,541
I'm perfectly fine.

46
00:01:59,624 --> 00:02:03,378
We can't be sure of that
until we've completed a full exam.

47
00:02:03,461 --> 00:02:05,880
If a virus was
the cause of Tup's breakdown,

48
00:02:05,964 --> 00:02:09,134
you have more than likely
been exposed to the contagion.

49
00:02:09,217 --> 00:02:12,387
You haven't entered
the advanced stages yet, as Tup has,

50
00:02:12,470 --> 00:02:15,015
but any information
we can gather from you

51
00:02:15,098 --> 00:02:17,392
could help to find a cure for Tup.

52
00:02:17,976 --> 00:02:20,603
All right, General, if it'll help Tup.

53
00:02:21,104 --> 00:02:25,358
Captain Rex, General Skywalker has
ordered you back to the war zone.

54
00:02:25,442 --> 00:02:27,569
You are to leave immediately.

55
00:02:27,652 --> 00:02:31,406
I'm sorry, Fives.
I wish I could stay, but duty calls.

56
00:02:31,489 --> 00:02:32,782
It's fine, sir.

57
00:02:32,866 --> 00:02:36,202
Fighting a virus is a nice
change of pace from all those clankers.

58
00:02:36,286 --> 00:02:38,163
Take care of yourself,

59
00:02:39,331 --> 00:02:40,665
and Tup.

60
00:02:54,137 --> 00:02:56,431
Let's begin the tests.

61
00:02:56,931 --> 00:02:58,933
Administer the stimulant.

62
00:03:06,274 --> 00:03:07,859
Remove his mask.

63
00:03:14,783 --> 00:03:16,451
What are they doing to Tup?

64
00:03:16,534 --> 00:03:17,577
Remain calm.

65
00:03:17,660 --> 00:03:19,120
Out of my way!

66
00:03:19,746 --> 00:03:22,040
Please return to the examination table.

67
00:03:25,627 --> 00:03:27,796
His reactions are normal.

68
00:03:28,380 --> 00:03:29,672
What's going on? General!

69
00:03:30,590 --> 00:03:31,800
General!

70
00:03:33,676 --> 00:03:34,761
No, no, no!

71
00:03:34,844 --> 00:03:36,388
Please return to the examination table.

72
00:03:36,805 --> 00:03:37,889
Come on!

73
00:03:37,972 --> 00:03:39,391
Remain calm.

74
00:03:39,474 --> 00:03:40,850
Please return to the exam...

75
00:03:43,978 --> 00:03:45,939
His reaction will subside.

76
00:03:46,022 --> 00:03:49,609
The patient must be awake
for the next round of tests.

77
00:03:49,692 --> 00:03:52,737
I am not fond of these hyper tests.

78
00:03:52,821 --> 00:03:57,450
Yes, but they do give us all the
information we need in a timely fashion.

79
00:04:00,036 --> 00:04:03,665
There does not seem to be
any sign of infection in the blood.

80
00:04:03,748 --> 00:04:05,333
How curious.

81
00:04:05,625 --> 00:04:08,503
The subject has tested
negative on all accounts.

82
00:04:08,837 --> 00:04:11,923
This clone seems to be
in perfect health.

83
00:04:12,507 --> 00:04:14,592
We must be missing something.

84
00:04:15,593 --> 00:04:16,761
Why am I here?

85
00:04:19,097 --> 00:04:20,682
Is he conscious?

86
00:04:21,558 --> 00:04:23,059
Follow orders!

87
00:04:23,143 --> 00:04:25,061
Kill Jedi. Kill Jedi!

88
00:04:25,145 --> 00:04:26,688
Are you finished with your tests?

89
00:04:26,771 --> 00:04:27,772
For now.

90
00:04:27,856 --> 00:04:29,107
Sedate him.

91
00:04:29,399 --> 00:04:30,442
Yes, ma'am.

92
00:04:30,525 --> 00:04:34,195
Orders. Follow orders. Follow orders.

93
00:04:34,446 --> 00:04:35,697
Follow orders.

94
00:04:37,365 --> 00:04:40,994
It appears this clone
has orders to kill a Jedi.

95
00:04:41,077 --> 00:04:44,456
Perhaps the Separatists found
a way to brainwash him.

96
00:04:45,206 --> 00:04:47,000
Look, is Tup going to be all right?

97
00:04:47,083 --> 00:04:48,418
Have they found anything out?

98
00:04:48,501 --> 00:04:50,462
Please, sit down.

99
00:04:50,545 --> 00:04:55,216
We are using hyper tests, so we should
be getting the results very quickly.

100
00:04:55,300 --> 00:04:58,261
We need to complete
more procedures on you.

101
00:04:59,053 --> 00:05:00,638
-Sorry.
-Why?

102
00:05:01,890 --> 00:05:03,391
-Hey!
-I said I was sorry.

103
00:05:04,142 --> 00:05:05,268
You must understand,

104
00:05:05,351 --> 00:05:08,771
organic beings are so much harder
to analyze than droids.

105
00:05:09,147 --> 00:05:10,315
Well?

106
00:05:10,398 --> 00:05:12,108
Everything seems normal.

107
00:05:12,192 --> 00:05:14,611
Great!
Well, that means they can let me out.

108
00:05:14,694 --> 00:05:16,988
I am afraid that is not possible.

109
00:05:17,071 --> 00:05:18,239
You must remain quarantined

110
00:05:18,323 --> 00:05:21,826
until we have pinpointed the exact
cause of the other clone's breakdown.

111
00:05:21,910 --> 00:05:24,287
We cannot risk any further casualties.

112
00:05:24,370 --> 00:05:27,415
Look, I am not a threat,
and neither is Tup!

113
00:05:27,624 --> 00:05:28,833
Are you certain?

114
00:05:30,418 --> 00:05:34,047
You're just a droid.
You don't know about real duty,

115
00:05:34,130 --> 00:05:36,007
about what it's like to have a brother.

116
00:05:36,341 --> 00:05:38,134
I am sorry.

117
00:05:38,218 --> 00:05:41,179
I always wanted
to have human feelings,

118
00:05:41,262 --> 00:05:43,264
but I do not. Goodbye.

119
00:06:03,201 --> 00:06:07,205
Maybe whatever is causing
his aggression is psychological.

120
00:06:07,288 --> 00:06:09,624
It seems to be an isolated case.

121
00:06:09,707 --> 00:06:12,877
The other clone has yet
to display any symptoms.

122
00:06:24,639 --> 00:06:27,225
I need an answer now.

123
00:06:27,308 --> 00:06:29,978
This isn't just
a physical manifestation of psychosis.

124
00:06:30,311 --> 00:06:32,605
You must have missed something.

125
00:06:34,065 --> 00:06:38,278
Might I suggest a second brain scan,
an atomic-level brain scan?

126
00:06:38,361 --> 00:06:39,696
This is unnecessary.

127
00:06:39,779 --> 00:06:42,699
The Phase 1 and 2 scans we did
are sufficient.

128
00:06:42,782 --> 00:06:45,994
He's too weak
for a Phase 5 atomic-level scan.

129
00:06:46,077 --> 00:06:50,081
I calculate the beneficial knowledge we
could gain from a Phase 5 atomic scan

130
00:06:50,164 --> 00:06:51,916
is worth the risk.

131
00:06:52,125 --> 00:06:55,378
The only way to discover
what has happened to this clone

132
00:06:55,461 --> 00:06:56,754
is to terminate him

133
00:06:56,838 --> 00:06:59,966
and do a full-scale autopsy
on the molecular level.

134
00:07:00,341 --> 00:07:01,926
We must be cautious.

135
00:07:02,010 --> 00:07:04,345
I do not believe
this is a physical ailment,

136
00:07:04,429 --> 00:07:07,724
but a mental condition caused
by possible Separatist brainwashing.

137
00:07:07,807 --> 00:07:09,183
I do not agree.

138
00:07:09,267 --> 00:07:11,269
This is a virus of some kind.

139
00:07:11,352 --> 00:07:14,188
I am in charge of this examination

140
00:07:14,272 --> 00:07:17,483
and I will decide
what is best for my patient.

141
00:07:17,567 --> 00:07:21,738
Actually, since the Republic and
the Jedi commissioned the clones,

142
00:07:21,821 --> 00:07:25,199
it is our responsibility
to oversee their care.

143
00:07:26,451 --> 00:07:28,369
Every clone and their genetic makeup

144
00:07:28,453 --> 00:07:30,705
is property of
the Kaminoan government.

145
00:07:31,372 --> 00:07:35,001
Now, as a client of ours,
I will respect your wishes,

146
00:07:35,418 --> 00:07:37,962
but as to the fate of this clone,

147
00:07:38,046 --> 00:07:41,007
I will speak to
our Prime Minister, Lama Su.

148
00:07:41,341 --> 00:07:45,178
And I will advise the Jedi Council
on the atomic brain scan

149
00:07:45,261 --> 00:07:47,680
and see how they would like to proceed.

150
00:07:47,764 --> 00:07:49,349
Very well.

151
00:07:54,187 --> 00:07:55,647
-Hello.
-What's going on?

152
00:07:55,730 --> 00:08:00,026
CT-5385's condition
seems to be deteriorating.

153
00:08:00,693 --> 00:08:03,071
Tup. His name is Tup.

154
00:08:03,863 --> 00:08:06,032
Tup? What is a Tup?

155
00:08:06,115 --> 00:08:08,993
Tup is my friend. He's not a number.

156
00:08:09,077 --> 00:08:11,663
Yes, he is. We all have numbers.

157
00:08:11,746 --> 00:08:17,335
My number is
AZ-345211896246498721347.

158
00:08:17,794 --> 00:08:20,088
His number is CT-5385.

159
00:08:20,338 --> 00:08:22,340
Wrong. He has a name.

160
00:08:22,423 --> 00:08:24,467
No clone uses a number.

161
00:08:24,717 --> 00:08:26,094
Not anymore.

162
00:08:26,177 --> 00:08:29,514
But you are a number, CT-5555.

163
00:08:29,931 --> 00:08:33,351
No, I am Fives. Call me Fives.

164
00:08:33,434 --> 00:08:35,978
But five is a number.

165
00:08:36,062 --> 00:08:38,606
No, not five. Fives.

166
00:08:41,442 --> 00:08:42,944
The difference is minimal.

167
00:08:43,027 --> 00:08:46,155
Not to me. And not to any clone.

168
00:08:50,702 --> 00:08:55,873
It appears there has been a preemptive
execution of Clone Protocol 66.

169
00:08:56,958 --> 00:08:58,835
How did this happen?

170
00:08:59,168 --> 00:09:00,878
I do not know as of yet.

171
00:09:00,962 --> 00:09:04,090
However, I recommend
we terminate the clone

172
00:09:04,465 --> 00:09:08,928
and do a full autopsy to discover
how the inhibitor chip was activated.

173
00:09:09,929 --> 00:09:12,056
And what of the Jedi?

174
00:09:12,140 --> 00:09:16,644
The Jedi Shaak Ti is proposing
an atomic-level brain scan.

175
00:09:17,562 --> 00:09:22,066
She has gone to the Jedi Council to
seek their approval before proceeding.

176
00:09:23,317 --> 00:09:25,987
We must contact Lord Tyranus.

177
00:09:41,878 --> 00:09:44,881
<i>I've been expecting your transmission.</i>

178
00:09:44,964 --> 00:09:47,842
<i>I have heard
of the malfunctioning clone.</i>

179
00:09:47,925 --> 00:09:49,969
<i>How widespread is the problem?</i>

180
00:09:50,303 --> 00:09:53,014
It seems to be an isolated incident.

181
00:09:53,556 --> 00:09:57,894
However, this is a delicate situation.

182
00:09:57,977 --> 00:10:01,314
We need to terminate the clone
as soon as possible

183
00:10:01,397 --> 00:10:06,819
in order to extract and analyze the
inhibitor chip that you provided to us.

184
00:10:06,903 --> 00:10:08,279
<i>Very good.</i>

185
00:10:08,362 --> 00:10:10,740
<i>Terminate the clone immediately.</i>

186
00:10:10,823 --> 00:10:14,202
<i>However, send the chip
to me for analysis.</i>

187
00:10:14,660 --> 00:10:19,624
And what if the Jedi ask for the chip
and the results of the autopsy?

188
00:10:19,707 --> 00:10:21,417
<i>You must remember,</i>

189
00:10:21,501 --> 00:10:25,797
<i>the chip is a safeguard
against betrayal from rogue Jedi.</i>

190
00:10:25,880 --> 00:10:30,009
<i>Master Sifo-Dyas
was the only Jedi who knew of this.</i>

191
00:10:30,927 --> 00:10:34,680
<i>But with his passing,
we alone know of this secret</i>

192
00:10:34,764 --> 00:10:37,308
<i>and you must keep it that way.</i>

193
00:10:37,391 --> 00:10:39,435
Yes, Lord Tyranus.

194
00:10:41,062 --> 00:10:44,440
These Jedi are a curious cult.

195
00:10:44,524 --> 00:10:47,026
Too spiritual for my taste.

196
00:10:47,109 --> 00:10:49,904
I will terminate the clone immediately.

197
00:10:51,072 --> 00:10:54,575
<i>The Kaminoans have suggested
that we terminate the clone</i>

198
00:10:54,659 --> 00:10:58,412
<i>and do a rigorous molecular autopsy
to discover the virus.</i>

199
00:10:58,496 --> 00:11:01,165
<i>I believe this solution is ill-advised.</i>

200
00:11:01,249 --> 00:11:04,335
<i>My belief is that Tup has been
brainwashed by the Separatists</i>

201
00:11:04,418 --> 00:11:08,005
<i>using some new process
we do not yet understand.</i>

202
00:11:08,089 --> 00:11:10,842
<i>Brainwashing?
How could that be possible?</i>

203
00:11:10,925 --> 00:11:14,387
<i>General Skywalker reported
Tup missing on Ringo Vinda,</i>

204
00:11:14,470 --> 00:11:17,390
<i>but after five rotations
he turned up again.</i>

205
00:11:17,682 --> 00:11:20,476
<i>That event preceded this episode.</i>

206
00:11:20,560 --> 00:11:23,688
<i>Perhaps he was compromised
at that point.</i>

207
00:11:23,771 --> 00:11:26,357
<i>We must find the truth
behind this situation,</i>

208
00:11:26,440 --> 00:11:29,944
<i>or we could find many more clones
turned against us.</i>

209
00:11:30,486 --> 00:11:33,531
<i>I would like to implement
a Level 5 atomic brain scan,</i>

210
00:11:33,614 --> 00:11:36,993
<i>to see if his thought processes
are still functioning normally.</i>

211
00:11:37,076 --> 00:11:39,370
And what do
the Kaminoans think of that?

212
00:11:39,453 --> 00:11:41,205
<i>They feel Tup is so weak,</i>

213
00:11:41,289 --> 00:11:45,001
<i>the Level 5 atomic brain scan
would damage his neural tissue</i>

214
00:11:45,084 --> 00:11:46,711
<i>and possibly kill him.</i>

215
00:11:46,794 --> 00:11:49,005
<i>Their approach
would be to terminate him,</i>

216
00:11:49,088 --> 00:11:52,425
<i>thus leaving the brain
fully intact for the autopsy.</i>

217
00:11:52,967 --> 00:11:55,761
Bring Clone Trooper Tup
back to the Jedi Temple.

218
00:11:56,012 --> 00:11:59,307
Yes. Examine him
with the Force we shall,

219
00:11:59,390 --> 00:12:01,642
and unravel this mystery we will.

220
00:12:02,643 --> 00:12:05,813
<i>Yes, Master.
I'll bring him back immediately.</i>

221
00:12:10,651 --> 00:12:13,571
No! There's too much
procedure and protocol here!

222
00:12:13,654 --> 00:12:16,741
Tup is a soldier.
He risks his life every day,

223
00:12:16,824 --> 00:12:18,910
and I know he would risk it now

224
00:12:18,993 --> 00:12:21,621
if it meant finding a cure
for what's wrong with him.

225
00:12:21,954 --> 00:12:24,206
I recommended an atomic brain scan,

226
00:12:24,290 --> 00:12:26,709
but that request has
thus far has been denied.

227
00:12:27,001 --> 00:12:31,672
Then we have to get the results
of that brain scan ourselves.

228
00:12:31,756 --> 00:12:34,175
But that is against protocol.

229
00:12:34,258 --> 00:12:38,512
Think about it.
It's your duty to save the patient, right?

230
00:12:38,596 --> 00:12:39,764
That is correct.

231
00:12:39,847 --> 00:12:42,892
And you recommended
this atomic brain scan

232
00:12:42,975 --> 00:12:45,519
as the best way
to save the patient, right?

233
00:12:45,603 --> 00:12:46,979
That is correct.

234
00:12:47,063 --> 00:12:53,903
So, by not performing this scan,
you are letting the patient die, willingly.

235
00:12:54,862 --> 00:12:57,698
Impossible.
That is against my programming.

236
00:12:58,991 --> 00:13:01,410
That's not the way it looks to me.

237
00:13:01,494 --> 00:13:05,331
I cannot perform the atomic brain scan
without disobeying orders.

238
00:13:05,414 --> 00:13:06,749
Check your programming.

239
00:13:06,832 --> 00:13:12,463
I thought saving the patient at all costs
was fundamentally your highest order.

240
00:13:12,546 --> 00:13:14,006
You are correct.

241
00:13:14,090 --> 00:13:16,842
Right. Then let's get to it!

242
00:13:20,888 --> 00:13:22,098
Quickly!

243
00:13:39,532 --> 00:13:43,077
Okay, let's get to work.

244
00:14:14,442 --> 00:14:16,610
The scan is almost complete.

245
00:14:21,866 --> 00:14:24,076
Everything appears to be normal.

246
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:25,661
Wait a second.

247
00:14:27,329 --> 00:14:28,789
What? What is it?

248
00:14:29,331 --> 00:14:32,501
It appears this clone
has developed a tumor.

249
00:14:33,586 --> 00:14:35,337
Is that even possible?

250
00:14:36,130 --> 00:14:39,508
I have never witnessed
anything like this in your kind.

251
00:14:39,592 --> 00:14:41,927
Well, then, what is it?

252
00:14:42,011 --> 00:14:44,221
I cannot be sure without a biopsy.

253
00:14:44,305 --> 00:14:46,474
You're gonna take it out of him?

254
00:14:50,936 --> 00:14:52,313
What was that?

255
00:14:52,396 --> 00:14:53,814
Do you think anybody heard that?

256
00:14:54,482 --> 00:14:57,985
The probability that somebody
heard that is high, yes.

257
00:15:05,076 --> 00:15:06,952
It came from this room.

258
00:15:14,752 --> 00:15:16,003
Hello, Doctor.

259
00:15:16,337 --> 00:15:17,880
What do you think you're doing?

260
00:15:18,380 --> 00:15:20,257
I was only following protocol.

261
00:15:20,341 --> 00:15:22,093
"Save the patient."

262
00:15:32,728 --> 00:15:36,357
Doctor, I have found something unusual
in this scan.

263
00:15:37,274 --> 00:15:41,112
It appears to be a tumor.
Perhaps you should take a look.

264
00:15:41,195 --> 00:15:45,407
You performed a second scan
without my authorization?

265
00:15:45,491 --> 00:15:48,536
As I stated,
I was following my programming.

266
00:15:49,995 --> 00:15:52,873
Then you are like this clone, defective!

267
00:15:54,959 --> 00:15:58,003
You will be put on report
for deactivation.

268
00:16:01,966 --> 00:16:03,634
But the tumor...

269
00:16:03,717 --> 00:16:06,095
This tumor seems to be
blocking neuro-impulses

270
00:16:06,178 --> 00:16:08,222
from communicating within the brain.

271
00:16:08,305 --> 00:16:09,807
We should scan the rest of the clones

272
00:16:09,890 --> 00:16:12,518
to see if this is a problem
with their base genetic model

273
00:16:12,601 --> 00:16:14,728
or a mutation with the current models.

274
00:16:14,812 --> 00:16:18,107
There is no tumor.
Your scan is incorrect.

275
00:16:18,190 --> 00:16:19,191
But...

276
00:16:19,275 --> 00:16:22,361
This clone clearly has
a virus that remains undetected,

277
00:16:22,444 --> 00:16:25,573
but I will find the cause
once he's terminated.

278
00:16:26,782 --> 00:16:28,325
Now leave.

279
00:16:41,547 --> 00:16:44,508
I can't believe it.
They're going to kill him.

280
00:16:44,592 --> 00:16:48,053
In a case like this,
it is the logical course of action.

281
00:16:48,554 --> 00:16:52,183
No! No! We were not created
to be disposed of this way!

282
00:16:52,266 --> 00:16:53,976
Perhaps you were.

283
00:16:55,352 --> 00:17:00,232
CT-5385 will be terminated
so that others like him could survive.

284
00:17:00,316 --> 00:17:02,234
There aren't others like him.

285
00:17:03,068 --> 00:17:04,695
Tup doesn't have to die.

286
00:17:04,778 --> 00:17:08,324
You found a tumor.
I'm sure that's the cause of all this.

287
00:17:08,407 --> 00:17:10,451
It's the only thing that makes sense.

288
00:17:10,534 --> 00:17:12,244
But how can we proceed?

289
00:17:12,328 --> 00:17:13,829
Do your biopsy.

290
00:17:13,913 --> 00:17:17,374
I'm sure what you find
will prove Tup does not have to die.

291
00:17:17,458 --> 00:17:18,959
But Nala Se does not believe...

292
00:17:19,043 --> 00:17:21,879
We're not going to Nala Se
with whatever you find.

293
00:17:21,962 --> 00:17:25,049
We'll go to the General, to Shaak Ti.

294
00:17:25,132 --> 00:17:27,134
She helped me once, as a cadet.

295
00:17:27,218 --> 00:17:29,261
I know she values the life of a clone.

296
00:17:29,345 --> 00:17:31,805
But we will be disobeying direct orders.

297
00:17:31,889 --> 00:17:34,308
Yep, for the second time today.

298
00:17:34,391 --> 00:17:36,727
Can you hack into
the medical center's mainframe?

299
00:17:36,810 --> 00:17:39,230
I do possess that ability, yes.

300
00:17:39,813 --> 00:17:42,650
All right.
Well, here's what you need to do.

301
00:17:50,783 --> 00:17:52,910
It will be a painless death.

302
00:17:52,993 --> 00:17:55,746
Soon all our questions
will be answered.

303
00:17:58,874 --> 00:18:00,459
You may proceed.

304
00:18:01,126 --> 00:18:03,128
Hurry! You got it? Are you in?

305
00:18:04,171 --> 00:18:05,506
Got it.

306
00:18:06,048 --> 00:18:08,968
<i>Intruder alert! Intruder alert!</i>

307
00:18:09,051 --> 00:18:12,846
<i>All non-essential personnel
report to a safe room for lockdown.</i>

308
00:18:23,482 --> 00:18:26,110
Master Jedi, status report?

309
00:18:26,193 --> 00:18:29,154
<i>Scanners have picked up
an intruder in section C-6,</i>

310
00:18:29,238 --> 00:18:31,448
<i>but we have no visual confirmation.</i>

311
00:18:31,532 --> 00:18:33,993
It could be the enemy
looking for our patient.

312
00:18:34,076 --> 00:18:35,244
<i>I'm on my way.</i>

313
00:18:35,327 --> 00:18:37,621
<i>Please report to a secure room.</i>

314
00:18:42,209 --> 00:18:43,711
Good work, AZI.

315
00:18:43,794 --> 00:18:46,797
You better get started
before they figure out it's a false alarm.

316
00:18:46,880 --> 00:18:48,299
Right away.

317
00:19:14,825 --> 00:19:17,828
You might want to turn away
for this part.

318
00:19:31,633 --> 00:19:32,885
I want a report.

319
00:19:33,177 --> 00:19:36,263
It appears to be a false alarm,
triggered from the medical bay.

320
00:19:36,347 --> 00:19:37,806
Medical bay?

321
00:19:37,890 --> 00:19:39,808
It's Fives! Come on!

322
00:19:44,438 --> 00:19:45,439
Is it done?

323
00:19:51,278 --> 00:19:52,446
It is now.

324
00:19:58,494 --> 00:20:00,162
What have you done?

325
00:20:00,245 --> 00:20:02,122
We've saved my friend's life.

326
00:20:02,206 --> 00:20:04,416
This tumor is the cause of his illness.

327
00:20:04,500 --> 00:20:06,168
Give me that.

328
00:20:07,294 --> 00:20:09,088
You can't be trusted.

329
00:20:10,631 --> 00:20:12,091
Stand down, Trooper.

330
00:20:13,050 --> 00:20:15,969
General. I have evidence, it's right here!

331
00:20:16,345 --> 00:20:19,556
I'm free. The mission... Free...

332
00:20:19,973 --> 00:20:21,642
-Tup.
-The mission... Free.

333
00:20:22,559 --> 00:20:23,685
The mission...

334
00:20:23,894 --> 00:20:25,229
What is he saying?

335
00:20:25,896 --> 00:20:28,148
Brother, what mission?

336
00:20:28,732 --> 00:20:31,110
You... You know the one.

337
00:20:32,152 --> 00:20:35,572
The mission, the one in our dreams,

338
00:20:35,656 --> 00:20:36,824
that never ends.

339
00:20:37,491 --> 00:20:39,493
The one in our dreams...

340
00:20:40,369 --> 00:20:41,620
Brother,

341
00:20:47,793 --> 00:20:49,962
this is the end.

342
00:20:50,045 --> 00:20:52,005
Forget the mission.

343
00:20:53,841 --> 00:20:55,467
The nightmare...

344
00:20:56,009 --> 00:20:58,345
I'm free.

345
00:21:00,514 --> 00:21:02,558
No. No.

346
00:21:04,518 --> 00:21:06,395
I thought I saved him.

347
00:21:12,860 --> 00:21:17,197
<i>Sir, the clone CT-5385 has died.</i>

348
00:21:17,739 --> 00:21:19,283
Such a tragedy.

349
00:21:20,617 --> 00:21:24,288
<i>I recommend we do further tests
on this tumor at the Jedi Temple,</i>

350
00:21:24,371 --> 00:21:26,415
<i>to see if it is the cause of the problem.</i>

351
00:21:26,498 --> 00:21:27,583
Or even better,

352
00:21:27,666 --> 00:21:31,545
have the tumor sent
to the Grand Republic Medical Facility

353
00:21:31,628 --> 00:21:33,088
here on Coruscant.

354
00:21:33,464 --> 00:21:36,300
<i>The Jedi Council requested the clone...</i>

355
00:21:36,383 --> 00:21:38,510
<i>I think the Chancellor is correct.</i>

356
00:21:38,594 --> 00:21:41,513
<i>The Grand Medical Facility
is state-of-the-art.</i>

357
00:21:41,597 --> 00:21:45,893
<i>If we are to find an answer to
this puzzle, we will find it there.</i>

358
00:21:45,976 --> 00:21:47,978
We are in agreement then?

359
00:21:49,062 --> 00:21:50,397
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

360
00:21:50,421 --> 00:21:55,421
http://hiqve.com/

